on high-intent users** (action/impact).\n\n### 1.3 Classification Type\n\nThis is a **binary classification** problem:\n- **Class 1 (Positive):** Customer converts  \n- **Class 0 (Negative):** Customer does not convert  \n\n### 1.4 Motivation and Real-World Impact\n\nThis project connects to **SDG 12: Responsible Consumption and Production**. By predicting conversion likelihood, businesses can:\n- **Reduce wasted ad spend** on low-intent users  \n- **Decrease unnecessary digital exposure** (fewer irrelevant ads for customers)  \n- **Improve return on ad spend (ROAS)** by focusing on high-probability segments  \n\n**Target KPI:** Reduce cost per conversion by 15% while maintaining or improving total conversions over a 3–6 month period.\n\n### 1.5 Stakeholder Analysis\n\n| Stakeholder | Benefit / Risk |\n|---|---|\n| Marketing Managers | Direct benefit of better targeting, lower cost per conversion |\n| CRM Teams | Direct benefit of personalized outreach to high-intent users |\n| Customers | Indirect benefit of fewer irrelevant ads, better experience |\n| Business (Finance) | Indirect benefit of improved ROAS and budget efficiency |\n| Low-intent customers | Potential risk of receiving less engagement or being deprioritized |","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Hypothesis\n\nBased on domain understanding of digital marketing, the following hypotheses will guide the analysis:\n\n**H1 — Engagement drives conversion:** Customers with higher website engagement (more pages per visit, longer time on site, more website visits) are significantly more likely to convert.\n\n**H2 — Channel effectiveness varies:** Certain campaign channels (e.g., PPC, Email) produce higher conversion rates than others (e.g., Awareness campaigns via Social Media).\n\n**H3 — Behavioral signals outweigh demographics:** Features like AdSpend, WebsiteVisits, and EmailClicks are stronger predictors of conversion than Age, Gender, or Income.\n\nThese hypotheses will be tested during exploratory data analysis and validated through feature importance analysis after model training.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Dataset Selection and Ethical/Licensing Considerations\n\n### 3.1 Dataset Overview\n\n| Attribute | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Source** | Kaggle — Digital Marketing Campaign Dataset |\n| **Records** | 8,000 customers |\n| **Features** | 19 input features + 1 target variable |\n| **Target** | `Conversion` (binary: 0 or 1) |\n| **Format** | CSV |\n| **Missing Values** | None |\n\n### 3.2 Licensing\nThe dataset is publicly available on Kaggle under standard Kaggle terms of use, suitable for educational and research purposes.\n\n### 3.3 Ethical Considerations\n\n- **Sensitive attribute identified:** `Gender` (Male/Female) — model fairness across gender groups will be evaluated in Section 6.\n- **Privacy protection observed:** `AdvertisingPlatform` and `AdvertisingTool` are anonymized as \"IsConfid\" and \"ToolConfid\", indicating the data provider has taken steps to protect commercial confidentiality.\n- **Potential leakage risk:** `ConversionRate` may encode the target variable directly. This will be investigated and addressed during preprocessing.\n- **No personally identifiable information (PII):** CustomerID is a numeric index, not linked to real individuals.\n\n### 3.4 Regulatory Risk Tier\nUnder the EU AI Act framework, this project falls under the **Limited Risk** tier. Marketing optimization does not involve biometric identification, medical decisions, or law enforcement. No DPIA is required, but fairness monitoring is still a good practice.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Core libraries\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\n# Preprocessing\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, StratifiedKFold, GridSearchCV, cross_val_score\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, LabelEncoder, OneHotEncoder\nfrom sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\nfrom sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n\n# Models\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\nfrom sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\n\n# Evaluation\nfrom sklearn.metrics import (\n    classification_report, confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay,\n    roc_auc_score, roc_curve, precision_recall_curve,\n    f1_score, accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score\n)\n\n# Imbalance handling\nfrom imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\nfrom imblearn.pipeline import Pipeline as ImbPipeline\n\n# Settings\nplt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\nsns.set_palette(\"husl\")\npd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n\nprint(\"All libraries loaded successfully.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.948973Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.949359Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.969193Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.949328Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.968293Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"All libraries loaded successfully.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":11},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df = pd.read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/datasets/rabieelkharoua/predict-conversion-in-digital-marketing-dataset/digital_marketing_campaign_dataset.csv\")\nprint(f\"Dataset shape: {df.shape}\")\ndf.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.970421Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.970760Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-18T12:22:56.071085Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-18T12:22:55.970716Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-18T12:22:56.069900Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Dataset shape: (8000, 20)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"execution_count":12,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"   CustomerID  Age  Gender 